25|$|Norwegian {{foundations}} origined {{along with}} settled estates (stamhus) and <b>fee</b> <b>tails</b> (fideikommiss) during absolutism in Norway, and noblemen {{were among the}} first to establish such. In 1814, when the Constitution of the Kingdom of Norway was introduced, the foundation system was the only to survive; the creation of new settled estates and new <b>fee</b> <b>tails</b> was prohibited.|$|R
