5000|$|Today, most jurisdictions {{recognize}} {{a system of}} definite failure of issue where property can be conveyed to a third party upon {{the death of a}} grantees heirs. Additionally, most jurisdictions have abolished <b>fee</b> <b>tails.</b> In jurisdictions that do recognize <b>fee</b> <b>tails,</b> most courts will {{recognize a}} [...] "fee upon indefinite failure of issue" [...] where the property returns to the original grantor if the tenant dies without issue.|$|R
